text: Two things I want to see in this movie - Some Tirek/Discord level evil - Anything unexpected -¬†MLP got me hooked by going beyond the call of duty for what a show called My little pony should be, so far the movie has really upped the scale with the new animation style, Equestria actually looks huge and movie-esque, I hope we get to actually see Ponyville as well because I really want to see it with this animation - Also Rainbow's sonic rainboom looks jaw-dropping, considering how well animated the original was considered by fans, this is some next level stuff and I'm certain it will look amazing in the cinema - My only real gripe I can notice so far is that the facial animation seem very restrained compared to the show, I hope Twilight gets more of her anger back as she's almost sleepwalking through all the scenes she's in and Pinkie looks off¬† and aside from Rainbow, the others don't seem to be doing anything but I'm sure they will - Another small problem is the action and slapstick seems a little restrained and soft compared to the show where the main character has been crippled before getting slammed with a flower pot, anvil, hay cart and piano -¬† And the last proper villain of the show pile-drived her through a mountain - I'm hoping to see this upped rather then downplayed - Anyway, this series has surprised me before, hopefully the movie can do the same.

Is this going to stay as a Theater experience and release it to DVD, and 10 years later release it to TV? Or the film bombs at the box office and they release it to the TV. text: Thoughts:  The spaceship thing seems strange, I know MLP plays fairly loose with the rules of fantasy but that's a little shark jumpy.  The sea ponies are a great idea though, I like world building. Twilight's word choice of "save Equestria" was interesting when talking to them. Are they part of Equestria? Are they allies of Equestria? If so it seems strange we've never heard of them. Maybe they were just persuaded to think Equestria was worth saving, but it is odd.   Anyway whatever I like the whole idea of exploring the oceans around Equestria and introducing the sea ponies like this.  Other thoughts, um the animation works very well for long shots, the awkward 3D effect is a bit weird in close ups though. So I hope they don't do too many close up shots. It is an action film so presumably they won't which is good lol. But yeah in long shots it works great, the characters looks great and the environments look mostly great as well.  But yeah I don't know, I'm all for pushing genre boundaries if it's done right but these alien things seem a bit forced in there, I'm not sure if that'll work. I hope it does work and I'm just whining about nothing, but I really don't know lol.  Anyway that's all, thanks for reading this whole thing lol, you have a lot of spare time if you got this far.

text: Even if you hate bronies, or hate MLP or whatever... Go find your sister, brother, a niece, nephew or cousin, and take them to see this film. Why? Because we need more 2D animated movies. 3D CGI is great and all, but it's everywhere. It's over saturated and 3D CGI movies are becoming more and more homogenized in terms of style, each trying to copy the others charms has made them look increasingly samey.  Go see this movie and let the studios know that 2D animation isn't dead, and that there's a demand for more!

However, I'm not a big fan of the so far extremely cliche henchman the new villain has with her, nor am I a fan of the Anthro Griffon and lion. As a whole, this trailer actually left me more worried than hyped--it had nice animations, and the villain looked interesting, but it seems like its falling back on tired Disney tropes instead of original ideas.  From this trailer alone, I'm willing to bet that either the Mane 6 Friendship the villain down, or she falls off a cliff and dies off camera. Either way, I'm expecting an early Millennial Disney movie, and I can honestly say I'm not happy with that.

text: WARNING: This is not a hate post, it's just an objective mixed with subjective opinion (pff, who am I kidding, this disclaimer will NEVER work... xD )  Can't say I'm a big fan of the new animation, I think Disney makes a better use of ToonBoom mixed with 2D (this was an OBJECTIVE opinion). The art itself is the most jarring thing to me, it'll take a lot of getting used to me, but that's my SUBJECTIVE opinion.   More OBJECTIVE opinions: What I'm really worried about, though, is the story and writing. I hope it won't be a common Hollywood blockbuster story, with the "bad guys come, need help from others, insert comic relief just because and painstakingly adhere to the typical three act structure" that I'm getting sick of in American animation movie, it's too predictable. Megan McCarthy always had this tendency when writing TV show finales, especially "A Canterlot Wedding" that could have been better.  More SUBJECTIVE opinions: But I DO like the broken-horned unicorn (great design and great potential backstory!) and the villain, also with a great design, keeps reminding me of MojoJojo in a good way. :D As for the Sea Ponies... well, world building, I guess, but at least their designs are good, at least compared to the godawful G1 designs... I also like the new Canterlot design: finally a BIG capital city!  BTW... where the heck is Starlight Glimmer? Did she go on vacation? o_O  But, as with most recent American trailers, they rarely give the right feeling of the movie. So I hope my writing and story worries are unfounded and the MLP G4 movie is something that Lauren Faust would be proud of. :)

text: I think it's really sad to see all the hate down here in the comments. To bronis and pegasisters; our fan base is about compassion and kindness, and the ability to get along with people, even though you have different opinions. To non bronies and pegasisters; this fan base is something we are part of. it brings us all together, and makes us all stronger, as well as better people. many of us are here because we felt excluded or left out. many of us are outcasts, and we came to this fan base because we knew that we would be accepted here. i implore you to tell me what is wrong with that. as absurd as it may sound, this show has helped many people with depression and sadness, me included. please, we would all be happier if we got along, and with that, this would be a much more peaceful place. you don't have to like the show, but you can at least accept that some people do. thanks :3

text: http://www.mensjournal.com/expert-advice/25-kids-movies-adults-will-actually-enjoy-20160104  Grow up and realize that the only people who live their life watching, reading or listening to things *exclusively* meant for their age bracket, are children. Adults enjoy whatever media they want, because they're adults living their own lives how they want, not children living under the rules of some one else.  ‚ÄúCritics who treat 'adult' as a term of approval, instead of as a merely descriptive term, cannot be adult themselves. To be concerned about being grown up, to admire the grown up because it is grown up, to blush at the suspicion of being childish; these things are the marks of childhood and adolescence. And in childhood and adolescence they are, in moderation, healthy symptoms. Young things ought to want to grow. But to carry on into middle life or even into early manhood this concern about being adult is a mark of really arrested development. When I was ten, I read fairy tales in secret and would have been ashamed if I had been found doing so. Now that I am fifty I read them openly. When I became a man I put away childish things, including the fear of childishness and the desire to be very grown up.‚Äù   ‚Äï C.S. Lewis

text: I don't get this... I am speaking on behalf of all of the bronies out there! I understand you guys hating this and disliking it, that's alright, but your getting the criticism way too far. I was scrolling down hate comments from this video and another and I kept seeing the same hate comment over, and over "Worst than the Emoji Movie!" "This is cancer!" "This is/You're gay!" That isn't right. You know what? We're not acting as kids, you are! You're acting like little toddlers who are hating what they get! Some of you are even copy and pasting other comments saying that this is stupid, for like a million times! Okay, tell me what you hate on this movie. Well, NOTHING!!! Cause it hasn't been released yet! And you are already judging this, not considering the fact that Emily Blunt, Taye Diggs, Kristin Chenoweth, Sia, etc. They are voice acting this very film! And also, Sia is writing a song for this! For some of them, this is their first movie or animated film they're voice acting it! Why waste your time hating when you can just ignore this and move on. This doesn't deserve the hate you have! I know that the previous generations are awful! I know that! Even the Bronies know that it is, but this is different. This show was once directed by Lauren Faust! Even though she is no longer the one that is leading the show, it still stays as a good show as we know. Also, did you know three of the writers of this movie are actually the same writers for Mulan and Toy Story? I'm not kidding! Check out the wiki of the film. This isn't bad as you think this is, so stop complaining and move on if you don't want to get involved. I'm not saying you must love this or you must watch it, I'm just keeping you aware that there are people out there who are working on this film and people watching it.

text: I'll be honest- I'm not a fan of how it looks. The animation itself is top-notch, But my biggest problem overall is the use of the 3D assets. Places like Canterlot, the Airship, and that propeller look really out of place- like something you'd see in one of those Direct-to-DVD Princess/Barbie/Tinkerbell movies. In stark contrast, the characters themselves look flat, but also poofy because of the shading...? They look like poofy stickers, and it looks really weird. It's even weirder when not all the backgrounds look like that! The bottom of the waterfall looks really good and not out-of-place, what's up with the rest of these places?  Tempest's little toadie looks like he'll be getting on my nerves- The Storm King COULD also, and Pinkie definitely will.  I'm sure it'll be okay, but I'm not seeing much that looks good (although the bad things aren't necessarily deal-breakers either)

text: Listen, if you don't like MLP, just don't click on the video. It makes me sad to see all of the hate here. Look, if you dislike MLP, PAW Patrol, Steven Universe, etc, I'm fine with that. It's another thing however to call the fans of these shows "autistic," "gay," and other things. We like what we like. Age and gender shouldn't matter, I'm turning 13 in September (I know it's immature to post your age in the comments to prove a point, but I don't care), and I still like Baby Einstein. Please don't bash on those who enjoy MLP or any other fandom. As for the people who make erotic fan fictions/porn of MLP, please stop. That is what is giving people a bad impression of the fandom. To those that are judging us because of that, don't judge a book by it's cover. We may look like a fandom that makes porn and inappropriate fanfiction, but we're actually a really kind, accepting group of people. Sure we have a few toxic members, but that happens in every fandom. Please stop bashing on people because they like one thing, please. Thank you for reading.

text: I know I'm a bit late to see this trailer, but wow... I have to admit from first glance, I'm a little shocked.  From the looks of it, it was made with a different animation tool than the show itself (I'm pretty sure it's Flash), and the art style also took me completely by surprise.  But not a bad surprise, it actually makes the ponies look really adorable, even if it took about a minute to get used to.    One thing I didn't like was how it hardly looks like it goes above even 30 frames per second.  Granted I don't think it will be that much of an issue, it's still fairly noticeable in parts.  Also the lip syncing looks sub par in some places.  On top of that the overall plot of the movie seems pretty overdone, especially in mlp in general.  "Great, powerful, evil enemy invades Equestria"... sound familiar?  Tirek, Chrysalis, even Discord kind of.  But I've seen this in so many other movies as well.  I can look past it though simply because it's mlp <3 And of course it looks like there's more going on in this trailer, so maybe it will have that extra creative burst I was hoping for when I first heard about this movie when I end up watching it.  Regardless, I'm really looking forward to seeing this movie.  It has pros and cons of course, but every movie does.  I really hope this will lock the show into a solid few more seasons, too.  I feel like the show is spiraling downward in terms of popularity, at least in the fandom.  It isn't what it used to be... maybe this will launch it into a new era.  I guess we'll see.

text: I know I might disappoint some of my fellow MLP fans, but I'm having mixed feelings about this movie ever since the show started going insanely downhill when Starlight was forcefully wedged into the main cast.   The animation is gorgeous and definitely makes it stand out from all the usual episodes' animation style, and the visuals and scenes absolutely have a breath-taking feeling going for them. I'll admit that.  But I'm alittle worried about how the cast and the movie will go. The lack of Rarity, Applejack, and Fluttershy, to the point of them not even getting a single line in this trailer deeply worries me. A giant flaw the most recent episodes had was making Pinkie Pie way over the top for the sole purpose of making her comedic relief and nothing else, to the point of showing no fear and being alittle "too" happy about even grim-looking situations, which 1:25 proves might keep her as solely a joke and not "real" character, which disappoints me already.   The new characters certainly are certainly well-designed and interesting, but not might fit really well into the MLP universe. I'm really iffy about this Tempest mare and her... seemingly alien force. (Which worries me, too... As throwing aliens into anything can utterly destroy it for me.) Aswell as her design having some very... IDK how to put it... I guess I'll use "OC design-ish" to describe her. Unicorns with broken horns has been rather cliched in the MLP community for tons of people and the name "Tempest" isn't the most original name out there.   I know I'm probably sounding super picky and rude, by now, but I'm sorry. I'd like to just get this off my chest.  I'm also iffy about the pirates. While, again, their design are unique and memorable, I feel like they're kinda outlandish, as well. They've been throwing tons of new species and creatures into MLP for a while now, and tons of new characters to the point where it's getting alittle difficult to remember them all. MLP already has tons of memorable characters and some bad ones, so I'm unsure if they have time or the writing to put in all these unique characters that will hopefully have time to develop over the course of the movie and not just be there because they look pretty. I suppose it's for the movie, so hopefully they'll be an important part of it. Along with maybe the seaponies. I'm the kind of person who likes to watch animal movies, and I've noticed a big flaw that most of the movies almost always suffer from: Making way too many characters for the story to follow, resulting in very few of them getting good development.  Lastly, the movie seems like it won't really be too touching, which in my opinion might hurt it. There's so many characters that seem like they'll be there just for comedic relief and jokes, so the real "conflict" doesn't seem like a real conflict when everyone's too busy cracking off jokes. I know it's an MLP movie, but I'd love an mlp movie that has touching and deep moments with a real heart to heart between characters instead of "I'll stop you!" and then Pinkie or side bad guy making a cake or pie joke. I'd love to see some heart-twisting moments and a real remember-able ending to this movie, and not just a laughfest that makes you feel no real tension.  I know I went off on quite a tangent about this. I'm really hyped up and interested in seeing this. I'm just worried deeply that the movie might just be "meh" instead of breath-taking. But... hey. Atleast Starlight Glimmer won't be hurting the movie by being in it, so that's a plus in my books.

text: I saw the film just yesterday, and, in my most honest opinion, I had mixed feelings. The film DID feature the same main characters (and their voice actors) from the TV series, showed more familiar characters in the background, introduced new areas and characters not seen in the series, had an assortment of good songs, and had beautiful animation.  However, there were a few small details about the film that didn't quite give it the same spark as the TV series.   First, the pacing of the film was just a little too quick, and didn't provide time for more possible drama and action moments; granted, the writers were limited to only one hour and thirty-five minutes.   Second, is that the humor that helped make the TV series fun for Brony fans to watch was stretched a little thin in the film.   Third, I think the personalities of the three antagonists (The Storm King, Tempest Shadow, and Grubber) could've used a little adjusting; The Storm King could've been more threatening (like Tirek from the Season 4 finale); Grubber could've been less awkward and food obsessed, and was more of a secretly loyal and dependable friend; Tempest could've been a little less mechanical and showed a little more fury and pangs of guilt and regret. Finally, I think the final confrontation between the Mane Six and the Storm King could've been a bit more epic; all of their allies from the past seasons (all the ponies of Equestria, The Crystal Ponies, Ember and the dragons, Thorax and the Changelings, and Dischord) rallying together to help defeat the Storm King.  I'm not saying it's bad film, I'm just saying that it's a little different from the TV series that Lauren Faust created.  Still, this is just MY personal opinion alone.  I hope this film satisfies the enjoyment of all other fans of MLP: FIM; especially for all you loyal and good-hearted Brony fans!

text: there are 3 major problems I have with this show  1: the main six are one dimensional and are basically stereotypes.  2: the show itself is sooo pandering towards little girls, and it doesn't expand upon it's concept or do anything new, thus why it's so pandering.  3: now this is probably the main problem I have with this show, the whole this with friendship being magic is stupid, because in real life, friendship doesn't do anything, it's not magic it's not power, it's just something people do to feel happy.   Now the reason why I think this is the main problem is because not only does it ruin to whole point of this (because it's slice of life show.) But it's a terrible thing for children to learn at a young age, because then they will think that friendship is the answer to all of their problems, and won't use basic problem solving to fix their problems.  Overall a good show that suffers from some major problems if fixed, could make my little pony a much better show and maybe even a masterpiece. Now there are some other problems with the show but these are the main ones.

text: In case if they ever make a sequel, maybe a second film, for the movie, they should add in a few more celebrities I can or could think of. The new cast I've been thinking should Christine Lakin as Lightning Rod and Lisa Wilhoit as Mighty Hurricane Furry witch are both sisters. For example, Lightning is Hurricane's oldest sister in this one. Harrison Ford and Meryl Streep as both the Dragon King, Raging Fire and Queen, Deltona, who raised the two sisters as their new daughters. Jason Bateman as Groblok, a kind of goblin. Brian Doyle-Murray as Cranky Old Man Acid, leader of the Basilisk clan. Jason Alexander as Rooksha, a kind of hobgoblin. Joaquin Phoenix as Flathead, a gremlin who pickpockets and loots for treasure and money. Winona Ryder as Magic Flight, who is an alicorn just like Twilight. Beverly D'Angelo or Anjelica Huston as the Witch Mare, Calamitous. And Amanda Seyfried and Amber Heard as the Magician Girls, Power Surge voiced by Amanda and Cosmic Chaos voiced by Amber. Plus they should bring back Kelly Sheridan as Starlight Glimmer, Rebecca Shoichet as Sunset Shimmer, Kathleen Barr as the Great and Powerful Trixie, Trixie Lunamoon, the Cutie Mark Crusaders, Sweetie Belle, Scootaloo and Apple Bloom both voiced by Claire Corlett, Michelle Creber, and Madeline Peters, Diana Kaarina as Aria Blaze, and Chiara Zanni as Daring Do for the movie. Plus, Shakira as Songbird's friend, Blue Tulips, an alicorn with a fantastic singing voice. And they should add in Mandy Moore as Whispering Winds, an alicorn who works for the Dragons and Karen Gillan as Deadly Nightshade, another secondary antagonist for the movie. The main villain should be played by Patrick Stewart who plays Raging Fire's oldest brother, Black Flame, the first king of dragons on Earth. But, if they do bring in a "Storm Queen," then, she should be voiced by non other than Dead Rising actress, "Kim Mai Guest." The stars are obviously Tara Strong as Twilight, Andrea Libman as Fluttershy and Pinkie, Ashleigh Ball as Rainbow Dash and Applejack, Tabitha St. Germain as Rarity and a few other additional voices and Cathy Weseluck as Spike along with Emily Blunt, Michael Pe√±a, Taye Diggs, Zoe Saldana, Uzo Aduba and Kristin Chenoweth. But the new characters for the second film should like the ones I mentioned. And I was thinking about the main villain should be played by David Warner, a British actor instead of Patrick Stewart and what not as maybe the first king of Dragons. Shining Armor should come back as well. Flim and Flam, voiced by Samuel Vincent and Scott McNeil, maybe Discord, voiced by John de Lancie as well. Gilda, Iron Will, don't care who. Catherine O'Hara should play someone too. Since they don't often ask old celebrities to play in movies anymore, I thought maybe they would be in the next movie too. Steve Martin would be a good choice too if he didn't cost a lot of money. But Shakira would do nice for Blue Tulips.
